    File

    A symbolic link to a file in a file system.
    FileSystem
    A file system has a root folder as the origin of its folder structure.

    A Folder is a file system entry that can store an unbounded number of entries.
    FolderLink
    A symbolic link to a folder in a file system.
    Link<T extends Entry>
    A symbolic link is a pointer to an entry in the file system.
